<img class="aligncenter wp-image-635" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Russia-Football-Team-300x190.jpg" alt="" width="543" height="344" />

<strong>Stadiums for FIFA World Cup 2018</strong>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Among all the 16 venue/Stadiums of the country some of the stadiums were dropped and finally, 12 stadiums are selected for FIFA World Cup 2018 these 12 stadiums are in 11 different cities. The capital city Moscow has 2 stadiums for FIFA World Cup 2018. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luzhniki_Stadium">Luzhniki Stadium</a> has the highest capacity among all the Stadiums that are going to be used for FIFA World Cup 2018. Among 12 stadiums 5 of them are newly built for FIFA World Cup 2018.and the final of FIFA World Cup will be kicked off at Luzhniki Stadium.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-636" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Luzhniki-Stadium-300x167.jpg" alt="" width="543" height="302" />
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luzhniki_Stadium">Luzhniki Stadium</a> with 81,000 capacities</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The ticket sells for FIFA World Cup 2018 has been already started from 14 September 2017 and have already closed after 12 October 2017 and the general policy of visa are excluded by Russia for World cups fans throughout the world.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The champions of FIFA World Cup 2018 will be awarded the prize money of 38 millions of American dollars and 28 million dollars for the runner-ups.</p>
